Label: Activity
Description: A specific climate modeling or analysis activity performed as part of a larger research effort

Label: City
Description: An urban settlement or municipality

Label: Continent
Description: One of the major landmasses on Earth

Label: Country_Subdivision
Description: A political or administrative subdivision within a country (e.g., state, province, region)

Label: Country
Description: A sovereign nation or political entity

Label: Domain
Description: A spatial or conceptual domain covered by climate model simulations

Label: Ensemble
Description: A collection of multiple model runs used to assess uncertainty and variability in climate projections

Label: Experiment
Description: A specific climate model experiment with defined conditions and objectives

Label: ExperimentFamily
Description: A group of related climate experiments sharing common characteristics or goals

Label: Field
Description: A scientific discipline or domain of study within climate research

Label: Forcing
Description: An external factor or condition that drives changes in the climate system (e.g., greenhouse gases, solar radiation)

Label: Frequency
Description: The temporal resolution or sampling rate of climate data output

Label: GridLabel
Description: A label or identifier for a specific grid configuration used in climate models

Label: Innovation
Description: A novel method, technique, or approach introduced in climate modeling research

Label: Institute
Description: A research institution or organization conducting climate science

Label: Instrument
Description: A measurement device or observational tool used to collect climate data

Label: Keyword
Description: A descriptive term or phrase characterizing research topics or content

Label: Member
Description: An individual member or realization within an ensemble of model runs

Label: Method
Description: A computational or analytical technique used in climate modeling or analysis

Label: Metric
Description: A quantitative measure or indicator used to evaluate model performance or climate characteristics

Label: MIPEra
Description: A Model Intercomparison Project era representing a coordinated phase of climate model experiments

Label: Model
Description: A computational representation of the climate system or its components

Label: Natural_Hazard
Description: A naturally occurring event that poses risks to human populations or ecosystems

Label: NaturalHazardType
Description: A category or classification of natural hazards

Label: No_Country_Region
Description: A geographic region not associated with any specific country (e.g., ocean, international waters)

Label: ObservationalDataset
Description: A collection of empirical measurements or observations of climate variables

Label: Ocean_Circulation
Description: Large-scale patterns of water movement in the oceans

Label: Paper
Description: A scientific publication or research article

Label: PhysicalFeature
Description: A tangible geographic or environmental characteristic (e.g., mountain range, ice sheet)

Label: PhysicalScheme
Description: A parameterization or representation of physical processes in climate models

Label: Platform
Description: A computational infrastructure or facility used for climate modeling

Label: Problem
Description: A scientific challenge or question addressed by climate research

Label: Project
Description: A coordinated research initiative or program in climate science

Label: RCM
Description: Regional Climate Model - a high-resolution model focusing on a specific geographic region

Label: Realm
Description: A major component of the Earth system (e.g., atmosphere, ocean, land, sea ice)

Label: Resolution
Description: The spatial or temporal granularity of model grid cells or data sampling

Label: Result
Description: An outcome, finding, or conclusion from climate modeling or analysis

Label: SimulationType
Description: A category of climate simulation (e.g., historical, future projection, control run)

Label: Source
Description: A climate model or data source providing simulation output

Label: SourceComponent
Description: A specific component or module within a climate model source

Label: SourceType
Description: A classification or category of climate model sources

Label: SubExperiment
Description: A subset or variant of a larger experiment with specific modifications

Label: Task
Description: A specific objective or analysis task in climate research

Label: Teleconnection
Description: A climate pattern or correlation between distant geographic regions

Label: Variable
Description: A measurable climate quantity or parameter (e.g., temperature, precipitation)

Label: Water_Bodies
Description: Bodies of water such as lakes, rivers, seas, or oceans

Label: Weather_Event
Description: A specific meteorological occurrence or phenomenon
